This paper involves the use of computer vision techniques to segment the prostate gland and intraprostatic lesions on MRI images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning models such as Mask-RCNN and U-Net suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of these techniques in the medical field suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.MED). The development of computer-aided diagnosis systems suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of MRI images suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
